---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Container from 'components/Container.astro';
import VideoGridSection from '@components/VideoGridSection.astro';
---
<Layout title="H4Sci">
	<main class="space-y-16 sm:space-y-28 lg:space-y-32 pb-40 overflow-clip">
	<Container >
	<div class="mb-12">
	<h1 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white font-bold text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl mt-16 mb-4">Course Materials</h1>
	<h2 class="text-gray-600 dark:text-white font-bold text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-3xl  mb-4">Prepare. Practice. Discuss. Apply.</h2>
	<p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 pb-4">
	Everyone has a different starting point, we all learn differently - particularly in a course where students from many fields come together.
    Hacking for Science aims to provide comfortable entry points to a wide variety of people who are interested in programming with data.
	</p>
	</div>

	<div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-16">
		<!-- Left column: 3 cards stacked -->
		<div class="space-y-6">
			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-lg">
				<p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
			    We have a highly <b>interactive online lecture</b> and <b>Matrix Chat channel</b> which want to coach as much as possible rather than teach.
			    Bring your questions and real world problems to class!
				</p>
				<a class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-500 mb-6" href="https://www.vorlesungen.ethz.ch/Vorlesungsverzeichnis/lerneinheit.view?lerneinheitId=192666&semkez=2025W&ansicht=LEHRVERANSTALTUNGEN&lang=en">Sign up for the 25/26 Course at ETH Zurich.</a>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-lg">
			<div class="max-w-48 w-full h-fit mx-auto mb-4">
			<p class="flex items-center space-x-2 mb-0">
			<img src="/h4sci-yt.png" alt="Hacking for Science on YouTube" loading="lazy" class="rounded-lg">
			<img src="youtube.svg" width="120" class="block dark:hidden flex-shrink-0"></img>
			</p>
			</div>
				<p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
				Information is ubiquitous.
				Time to practice, commitment and endurance is limited and has opportunity costs.
				Hacking for Science offers a series of digestable videos.
			    Our videos motivate, explain concepts and walk you through processes.
			    Step by step and in applied fashion.
				</p>
				<p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
				Explore our videos below | <a class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-500 mb-6" href="Sign up">H4Sci YouTube Channel</a>
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-lg">
			<div class="max-w-48 w-full h-fit mx-auto mb-4">
			<img src="quiz.png" width="400" class="block dark:hidden flex-shrink-0"></img>
			</div>
				<p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
				The ability to gut check not only your raw knowledge but your level of comfort is important when developing a more tech assisted personal workflow.
				Hacking for Science provides some easy quizzes to find out whether you are rather to take the most out of the next discussion or lecture.
				</p>
				<p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
					<a href="Sign up">Explore the quizzes! </a> | <a class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-500 mb-6" href="https://h4sci.github.io/h4sci-tasks/index.html">H4Sci Quizzes</a>
				</p>

			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Right column: Book card -->
		<div>
			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-lg h-full">
				<div class="max-w-48 w-full h-fit mx-auto mb-4">
	                <img src="/rse_book2.jpeg" alt="Research Software Enginnering - A Guide to the Open Source Ecosystem" loading="lazy" width="2481" height="1626" class="rounded-lg">
	            </div>
				<p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
				Given the abundance of information, it is often hard to extract the right information and a handable amount of that information.
				The book project Research Software Engineering - A Guide to the Open Source Ecosystem suggests a carefully curated dose of software engineering
			    for non-computer scientist data enthusiasts to learn.
			    The book is available in a free online version as well as a printed book from CRC/Chapman & Hall.
				</p>
				<a class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-500 mb-6" href="https://rse-book.github.io">Read Online on GitHub | </a><a class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-500 mb-6" href="https://www.amazon.com/Research-Software-Engineering-Ecosystem-Chapman/dp/1032261277">Order at Amazon</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Container>
<VideoGridSection/>
	</main>
</Layout>
